result.execSummary:
The defendant Christine Ann Stoffel was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Possess/Illegally Obtained Prescription, an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 450.11(7)(h).
  • Possess Drug Paraphernalia, an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 961.573(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Case Called @ 9:49 AM: Defendant Christine Ann Stoffel in court with attorney Ryan Scott Ulrich, both appearing in person.  Steven Paul Anderson appeared for the State of Wisconsin.   Counsel admit receipt of Rev Order and Warrant.  No factual corrections offered.  Victims Rights in Compliance.  Argument by ADA - will argue to divert from DOC's recommendation - 6 mos as to Ct 1 w/add'l 30 days Ct 2 consecutive terms.  70 days TS credit.  Argument by Atty Ulrich - argues for a sentence less than the State and DOC recommendation of somewhere in the 120 day range of WCJ.  Statement by Def:  Yes.   State offers for Court's review a letter rec'd from Def's parents.  Court reviews same and returns to ADA.  Atty Ulrich also reviewed letter.  The Court:   Motivation exists for recovery - priorities must be aligned.  As to Ct 1:  5 mos WCJ  Ct 2: 30 days WCJ - concurrent terms on WCJ.  Approx another 2 mos to serve.  TS credit granted of 70 days.  Costs reimposed - 60 DTP or PP.  No objection to balance of SEH being served in FDL if can be arranged.  Huber granted and GT.   Appeal Rights Given.

records.addlTxt: 15CF104 & 15CF35 called at 10:37 am. Defendant Christine Ann Stoffel in court with attorney Ryan Scott Ulrich.  Steven Paul Anderson appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Agreement reached.   15CF104-Complaint Stated - Advised of offense and minimum/maximum penalty.  Receipt Admitted - Reading Waived.  Preliminary Hearing and Time Limits discussed. Defendant wishes to waive preliminary hearing. Court questions defendant and accepts waiver of preliminary hearing. Court finds probable cause and enters an order binding the defendant over. Information filed. Attorney Ulrich confirms receipt, waives formal reading. 15CF35 & 15CF104-State moves to amend Count 1 of 15CF35 to Possess Illegally obtained Rx in violation of 450.11(7)(h).   Defendant advised of minimum/maximum penalty.  Plea QN reviewed w/Defendant.  Plea colloquy entertained.  Collateral consequences explained. Chapter 950 compliance addressed.  Plea: 15CF35-No Contest to Count 1 as amended &  No Contest to Count 2. No Contest to Count 1 of 15CF104. Court accepts plea and enters JOC. Court dismisses and reads-in Counts 2 & 3 of 15CF104.  Statement by defendant. Statement by Court prior to sentencing. Court senteces the defendant to: All Counts- SWD and places on probation for a period of 2 years. If revoked, 2 days of CTS. CONDITIONS: AODA and follow through, Maintain absolute sobriety, Not to be on the premises of any bars, Not to possess or ingest any impairing substances that have not been prescribed by a physician. Costs to be paid within 60 days or payment plan, including DNA surcharge.  Court orders bond on file be applied. Appeal Rights.
